| Description                      = ''While on a morning coffee and donut run for the team, Ant-Man discovers that someone has stolen his van that holds the Quantum Tunnel! Turns out it was Thanos and he’s partnered with Red Skull to travel back in time to recruit a powerful army of villains, including Iron Monger, Ultron, Hydra…and another Red Skull? It’s now up to Ant-Man and The Avengers to find Thanos and prevent him from changing history and destroying the world. Oh, and reclaim Ant-Man’s van, too. Avengers assemble!''

| Plot                      = '''Part 1: The Van Driver'''

In Manhattan, Scott Lang leaves a coffee shop carrying several coffees and boxes. A kid passes by on a skateboard and almost knocks him over, and Scott decides to Shrink the things. As he walks, Scott complains about being the Avengers' handyman. He discovers that his van has been stolen. 

On a tropical desert island (Hydra's secret base), Hydra soldiers and the Chitauri hang out on the resort. Below, Scott's van is playing music, irritating Thanos. Red Skull Thank Thanos for coming to the island but   the sound of the van is annoying. The Chitauri make the van stop and end up opening it, revealing the Quantum Tunnel. Thanos says he will use it to go back in time to gather what he needs to defeat the Avengers and recovering the Infinity Stones. The Chitauri activate the Quantum Tunnel and prepare for the trip. Thanos says that to defeat Iron Man they would need "Iron against Iron." 

In the not so distant past, Pepper leaves Stark Industries and Tony is on guard. the Iron Monger emerges from the ground preparing to attack Pepper. Tony arrives in time and the two battle. Obadiah defeat him and prepares to shoot.

'''Part 2: Red Skull Squared'''

Before Obadiah can shoot, Tony fires a beam from the Arc Reactor. From a portal, the Chitauri grab Iron Monger and take him away. 

In the present, at Hydra Base, the Chitauri and Iron Monger emerge from the portal created by the Quantum Tunnel. Thanos says that it could give Obadiah a magnificent power to defeat Iron Man. 

At the Avengers Tower, Tony is confused by the van being stolen. the rest of the team enjoys the donuts and coffee. Clint asks Scott if he kept the Quantum Tunnel in the van and he confirms, knowing that they could use it to go back in time and cause a lot of trouble. Tony says that he could have a way to detect quantum fluctuations or Pym particles but Scott shows that they could use the X-Con "Find My Car" app. He uses it and discovers that the van is on "a desert island in the middle of the ocean", which leaves them confused about who could have taken it and the reason why.

At Hydra's secret base, while the Chitauri upgrade Iron Monger's armor, Thanos orders  Schmidt to get the Tesseract and not get distracted with his revenge, Schmidt enters the portal created by the Quantum Tunnel. 

In the distant past, in Red Skull's jet, he and Captain America fight for the Tesseract. A lightning strike hits the jet and makes the Tesseract fall to the ground. From the portal, Future Schmidt appears and takes the Tesseract and laughs evilly.  

'''Part 3: Secret Agent Ant-Man''' 

Future Schmidt reveals himself to be from the future and came from the past to defeat Captain America and retrieve the Tesseract. Future Schmidt suggests Past Schmidt that they defeat Captain America together and then he would tell how to dominate the world and universe. The two start shooting lasers. Rogers dodges everything but is hit by one and reflects two with the shield, which hit and explode the Jet's controls and begins to fall. A portal to the Tunnel opens and Future Schmidt prepares to go back, saying that the future needed him and that he was saving his past self by saving himself. Rogers hits the Tesseract with the shield and recovers. The shield rebounds and hits Past Schmidt and the two enter the portal. 

Back at Hydra Base, Thanos deduces Red Skull's failure due to the lack of the Tesseract. Schmidt tries to persuade Thanos for bringing it himself but Thanos grabs Past Schmidt and throws him back into the portal. 

On a bug, Scott flies to the Island and discovers it is a Hydra base and the Chitauri are involved. Tony asks to find out who is in charge. A beach ball hits Scott, who falls onto a tray with coconuts. The henchman who was carrying the tray enters a public bathroom that has an elevator that takes him underground. Scott sees his van and discovers that Red Skull, Iron Monger and Thanos are involved. Thanos almost discovers Scott. Thanos says he needs one more personality and then he would crush the Avengers and dominate the world and universe. Thanos enters a Quantum Tunnel's Portal. 

A little after the not so distant past, in Sokovia, Ultron calls his Ultron sentinels and the Avengers battle them. Iron Man, Thor and Wanda use their combined powers and destroy Ultron's arm. Hulk finishes by kicking him away and scaring the sentinels. Ultron meets with Thanos.

'''Part 4: New Age of Ultron''' 

Thanos grabs Ultron and takes him to the Quantum Tunnel Portal. 

In the present, at Avengers Tower, Tony shows the Sakaaran Hulkbuster that he would use to battle Thanos, Hydra and Iron Monger and that Natasha would use the Hulkbuster. Rogers feels it from the outside. In the Deposit, Tony reveals an old armor created by his father. Rogers tests it and Natasha and Tony climb on it. 

Back on the Island, Thanos gives a speech to the Sentinels. Scott, on top of an Ultron Sentinel, warns Tony about the army. Tony asks him to delay. Scott throws a strawberry donut, making it grow in size and hit the Sentinels. Schmidt deduces that there is an intruder. Scott ends up growing in size and telling the Sentinels to share the donut. Thanos tries to hit him with his double-edged sword but Scott shrinks and Thanos pins the sword to the ground. Tony, Rogers and Natasha arrive in the armors along with Clint, Hulk, Thor and Wanda in the Quinjet. T'Challa arrives in his Jet. Scott is thrilled that everyone came to help him and is hit by Ultron. Hydra Soldiers attack in their tanks. Wanda and Hulk jump and help Scott with the Sentinels and Hydra Soldiers. Natasha destroys a Tank imitating Hulk saying "Widow Smash!". Tony destroys the Two Chitauri, hits two tanks and turns the Hulkbuster into a car. But is destroyed by Thanos. Thanos is hit by a Lightning from Thor. Tony, Thor and Wanda battle Thanos together. They use their combined powers and Thanos throws the sword away. Rogers battles the Chitauri, Sentinels and Hydra Soldiers with the Armor. The tank comes to him.

'''Part 5: Avengers, Assemble!'''

Rogers manages to stop the Tank. His armor begins to be destroyed by Red Skull's tanks. Scott shrinks the tanks with the shrinking discs. Rogers calls Scott "Partner" and makes him emotional but is hit by Ultron again. Rogers hits Ultron's shield and reflects the ray at him. T'Challa hits the Chitauri and several Sentinels begin to break the Ship and abandon the ship. Clint rescues with the Quinjet. Hulk catches Iron Monger while shooting at the Quinjet and the two battle. Thanos hits Tony but is held back by Wanda's magic. The two combine their powers on the Sword but Thanos is too powerful. Rogers is surrounded by the Sentinels and Natasha arrives but is hit by a Hydra Tank thrown by the Sentinels. With a shrinking disc, Scott asks everyone to retreat and saying "Avengers, Disassemble!" Missing Rogers' catchphrase. Natasha catches Rogers with the armor. Thor hits Thanos with Stormbreaker. Clint hits Iron Monger with the Quinjet while being chased by the Chitauri. Thor and Thanos battle and Thor is thrown away, standing next to Scott. Surrounded by the Sentinels, Hydra Soldiers, Chitauri, Thanos and Iron Monger, Scott grows in size and holds Thor, who flies alongside the rest of the team. Scott takes his van and throws the last shrink disc at the Island, shrinking it. Natasha asks why Scott didn't shrink and he replies saying he never had that idea. Scott turns on the music in the van. 

At the Avengers Tower, Scott thanks them for their help and shows that he brought more donuts and coffee. Scott shows that he put the Island inside a bottle with Tony's help. Inside the bottle, the Chitauri, Hydra Soldiers, Sentinels, Obadiah and Ultron enjoy the Resort while Thanos is angry.  

